{{Infobox Software | name = IsoBuster | logo = | screenshot = [[File:IsoBuster.png|300px]] | caption = IsoBuster 2.5 | developer = Smart Projects | latest release version = 2.8.5 | latest release date = {{release date|2010|12|20}} | latest preview version = | latest preview date = | operating system = [[Microsoft Windows]] | platform = | language = 27 languages<ref name="lang" /> | genre = [[Data recovery]] | license = [[Shareware]] ($29.95 [[USD]]) | website = {{URL|http://www.isobuster.com}} }} '''IsoBuster''' is a utility for CD and [[DVD]] data recovery. <ref>{{cite web |title=Recover file data from DVD, CD, BD and HD DVD discs (data rescue software) |url=http://www.isobuster.com/isobuster.php |publisher=Smart Projects |accessdate=2007-01-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.langa.com/newsletters/2003/2003-07-28.htm#4 |title=The Ultimate CD/DVD Data Recovery Tool |publisher=Fred Langa |accessdate=2003-07-28 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20030812131802/http://www.langa.com/newsletters/2003/2003-07-28.htm#4 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2003-08-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.komando.com/tips/index.aspx?id=1186 |title=Diagnosing problems with burned CDs |publisher=[[Kim Komando]] |accessdate=2006-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.infopackets.com/news/hardware/2005/20050603_remove_scratches_from_cd_or_dvd_compact_disc_part_2.htm |title=Remove Scratches from CD or DVD compact disc?, Part 2 |publisher=Dennis Faas - InfoPackets |accessdate=2005-06-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tpcug.org/newsletter/nl_2003/december2003/iso_buster.htm |title=IsoBuster for CD/DVD Data Recovery |publisher=Bob Lafave - Tampa PC Users Group |accessdate=2003-12-01}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.smalladdictions.com/Skateboard/articles/techbytes-149.htm |title=IsoBuster from Smart Projects |publisher=Francine Brokaw |accessdate=2005-02-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.isobuster.com/reviews.php |title=IsoBuster, best price quality solution |publisher=Markus Landau - [[CHIP_(magazine)|CHIP Magazine]] |accessdate=2006-02-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/jan03/articles/pcmusician0103.asp |title=Recovering Data From CDs (Last article on page) |publisher=Martin Walker - Sound On Sound |accessdate=2003-01-01}}</ref>
All CD and DVD formats are supported, including [[HD DVD]] and [[Blu-ray Disc|Blu-ray]]. It has the ability to access "deleted" data on multi-session [[CD-R]] and [[DVD-R]] discs, and allows users to access disc "images" in many formats (including [[ISO image|ISO]], BIN and NRG) and to extract files in the same way that they would from a [[ZIP (file format)|ZIP archive]]. IsoBuster is also well known and often used by law enforcement and data forensics experts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forensicmag.com/articles.asp?pid=127 |title=Digital Insider: Software Imaging/Analysis Tools and Hardware Devices -- Part 3 |publisher=John J. Barbara - Forensic Magazine |accessdate=2007-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.giac.org/certified_professionals/practicals/gcfa/0018.php |title=IsoBuster as a Forensic Tool |publisher=Steven D Dietz. |accessdate=2002-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forensicswiki.org/index.php?title=Forensic_file_formats |title=AccessData's Forensic Toolkit (FTK) uses built in IsoBuser technology for optical media |publisher=ForensicsWiki. |accessdate=2009-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forensic-computing.ltd.uk/tools.htm |title=Forensic software tools for Windows |publisher=Forensic Computing Ltd. |accessdate=2009-04-02}}</ref>
IsoBuster is produced by Smart Projects (founded in 1995 by Peter Van Hove) in Belgium. A functionality-restricted version is available freely. Extra functionality may be unlocked through purchasing a license key.
